methods.name: public Builder setSampleMimeType(@NonNull String value)
methods.comment: * Sets the MIME type of the video/audio/text samples.

methods.name: public Builder setBitrate(@IntRange(from = -1, to = Integer.MAX_VALUE) int value)
methods.comment:
* Sets bitrate in bits per second.
         * @param value the bitrate in bits per second. -1 indicates the value is unknown.

methods.name: public Builder setTimeSinceCreatedMillis(@IntRange(from = -1) long value)
methods.comment:
* Sets timestamp since the creation in milliseconds.
         * @param value the timestamp since the creation in milliseconds.
         *              -1 indicates the value is unknown.
         * @see #getTimeSinceCreatedMillis()

methods.name: public Builder setLanguage(@NonNull String value)
methods.comment:
* Sets language code.
         * @param value a two-letter ISO 639-1 language code.

methods.name: public Builder setLanguageRegion(@NonNull String value)
methods.comment:
* Sets language region code.
         * @param value an IETF BCP 47 optional language region subtag based on a two-letter country
         *              code.

methods.name: public Builder setChannelCount(@IntRange(from = -1, to = Integer.MAX_VALUE) int value)
methods.comment:
* Sets channel count.
         * @param value the channel count. -1 indicates the value is unknown.

methods.name: public Builder setAudioSampleRate(@IntRange(from = -1, to = Integer.MAX_VALUE) int value)
methods.comment:
* Sets sample rate.
         * @param value the sample rate. -1 indicates the value is unknown.

methods.name: public Builder setWidth(@IntRange(from = -1, to = Integer.MAX_VALUE) int value)
methods.comment:
* Sets video width.
         * @param value the video width. -1 indicates the value is unknown.

methods.name: public Builder setHeight(@IntRange(from = -1, to = Integer.MAX_VALUE) int value)
methods.comment:
* Sets video height.
         * @param value the video height. -1 indicates the value is unknown.

methods.name: public Builder setVideoFrameRate(@FloatRange(from = -1, to = Float.MAX_VALUE) float value)
methods.comment:
* Sets video frame rate.
         * @param value the video frame rate. -1 indicates the value is unknown.

methods.name: public Builder setMetricsBundle(@NonNull Bundle metricsBundle)
methods.comment:
* Sets metrics-related information that is not supported by dedicated * methods. *

It is intended to be used for backwards compatibility by the * metrics infrastructure.
